TMB quantifies the number of somatic mutations per megabase (mut/Mb) within a tumor genome. High TMB increases the likelihood of generating neoantigens—non‑self peptides presented by HLA molecules—that can be recognized by T‑cell receptors (TCRs). Neoantigen abundance correlates with tumor immunogenicity, fostering CD8⁺ T‑cell infiltration and cytokine secretion (IFN‑γ, TNF‑α).  

